entities.description: The number of motor vehicles recovered, with the variable type as numeric.
The frequency of cases observed without weighting adjustments, related to the number of recovered motor vehicles.
Statistical measures related to the recovered motor vehicles including mean, median, mode, minimum, maximum, and standard deviation.
The proportion or number of cases with missing data in the study.

relationships.description: Indicates the frequency of cases observed without weighting adjustments.
Relates the number of recovered motor vehicles to various statistical measures.
Indicates the number or proportion of cases with missing data in the survey.
